\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The AFDA - The South African School of Motion is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education institution with programmes that are accredited by the CHE. \line \line The Institution is applying for the accreditation of a Bachelor of Creative Writing programme which will be offered in the contact mode of delivery at the following campuses\'3A AFDA - Auckland Park\'2C Johannesburg\'2C AFDA Cape Town- Observatory\'3B AFDA Durban - Glen Anil\'2C Durban and AFDA Port Elizabeth - Nelson Mandela Bay.\line \line The Institution currently offers the following accredited programmes in the same field\'3A \line - Higher Certificate in Film\'2C Television and Entertainment Production\'3B \line - Bachelor of Arts in Live Performance\'3B \line - Bachelor of Arts in Motion Picture Medium\'3B \line - Bachelor of Arts Honours in Live Performance\'3B \line - Bachelor of Arts Honours in Motion Picture Medium\'3B \line - Bachelor of Commerce in Business Innovation and Entrepreneurship\'3B and \line - Master of Fine Arts in Motion Picture Medium. \line \line The AFDA also applied for the accreditation of the following programmes\'3A\line - Postgraduate Diploma in Innovation\'3B\line - Higher Certificate in Performing Arts\'3B \line - Higher Certificate in Radio and Podcasting\'3B \line - Higher Certificate in Interactive Entertainment and Game Design.\line \cell \pard 

